INSTALLING debconf plugin

Files:
Copy the folder admin/debconf in fusiondirectory/plugins/admin
Copy bin/debconf2ldif.pl in a bin folder, for instance /usr/local/bin

Schema:
Add debconf schema to your LDAP:
# cd contrib/openldap
# fusiondirectory-schema2ldif debconf.schema > debconf.ldif
# fusiondirectory-insert-schema -i debconf
# fusiondirectory-schema2ldif debconf-fd.schema > debconf-fd.ldif
# fusiondirectory-insert-schema -i debconf-fd

Config file:
In fusiondirectory.conf, in <section name="Administration">, add:
    <plugin acl="debconfProfile" class="debconfProfileManagement" />

Cache:
Run:
# fusiondirectory-setup --update-cache


USING debconf plugin

Then you should see a Debconf Profile entry in your admin menu.
Go there, clic Action->Create->debconfProfile
Follow the instruction to create an LDIF file using debconf2ldif
Import the created file.
Then open a workstation, you shoud have a debconf tab. In this tab, activate debconf and select the profile you just imported.
For more detailed instruction, read https://forge.fusiondirectory.org/projects/debconf/wiki/Howto
